<p>John August wants Apple to eliminate the &#8220;top charts&#8221; from the App Store:</p><blockquote><p>These lists &#8212; a sidebar in iTunes, a tab on the App Store &#8212; show
what’s downloaded the most. But let’s not mistake downloads for
popularity. These are apps that people may have downloaded, used
once, then deleted. What you really want is a list that shows what
apps that people <em>like you</em> are using and enjoying. That’s the kind
of information that companies like Amazon and Netflix are terrific
at leveraging.</p></blockquote><div><a  title=\"Permanent link to ‘&#8216;Topping the Charts and Racing to the Bottom&#8217;’\"  href=\"http://daringfireball.net/linked/2013/06/06/august-charts\">&nbsp;★&nbsp;</a></div>

